## Common HTTP Methods and Risk Analysis

| Method  | Description                      | Risk Level |
| ------- | -------------------------------- | ---------- |
| GET     | Retrieve data                    | Low        |
| POST    | Submit data                      | Low        |
| HEAD    | Headers only                     | Low        |
| OPTIONS | Lists allowed methods            | Medium     |
| PUT     | Upload files                     | High       |
| DELETE  | Delete resources                 | High       |
| TRACE   | Echo request (XST vulnerability) | Medium     |
| CONNECT | Proxy tunneling                  | Medium     |

---

## Interpreting Results

### Safe Configuration

```
Supported Methods: GET HEAD POST
```

* Only essential methods are enabled.

### Potentially Vulnerable Configuration

```
Supported Methods: GET POST PUT DELETE TRACE OPTIONS
```

This indicates:

* File upload capability (`PUT`)
* File deletion (`DELETE`)
* Possible XST attack (`TRACE`)

